block.info: A short introduction into just-in-time compiler techniques is given: Why JIT, about compiler invocation, runtime code modification using signals, codegeneration. Then theoretical attack vectors are elaborated: language bugs, intermediate representation quirks and assembler instruction inadequacies.With these considerations in mind the results of a CACAO code review are presented. For each vulnerability possible exploits are discussed and two realized exploits are demonstrated. /
block.data: A short introduction into just-in-time compiler techniques is given: Why JIT, about compiler invocation, runtime code modification using signals, codegeneration. Then theoretical attack vectors are elaborated: language bugs, intermediate representation quirks and assembler instruction inadequacies.With these considerations in mind the results of a CACAO code review are presented. For each vulnerability possible exploits are discussed and two realized exploits are demonstrated.
